or knowledge to include basic rent enq</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">uiries whic</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">h enables them to take payments. This enables our customers to access specific support including debt, budgeting and appropriate arrangements. </span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 14.33pt; padding-left:13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Analysis of our Benefit and Money Advice service using a case management system, has demonstrated the</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> need to provide more debt focused support for Yorkshire Housing customers. With 1105 referrals into our service the team have accessed £163.5K in benefits and charitable trusts enabling customers to pay their rent and £322K of other customer debt. The shi</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ft in the provision of the service, over the 10 years the team have been working with customers, has shown a move away from supporting benefit applications towards a more holistic approach to improving their ability to sustaining their tenancies. The decis</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ion to support this is further evidenced by the Northern Housing Consortium report – Real Life Reform Sept 2013, which highlights the average level of debt per household as being £2418. From our figures our average customer debt is £4389. This is a regiona</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">l figure and we know that this varies across the region. Our resource planning is taking this into consideration.</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 17pt; padding-left:13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The demand for quality and timely advice has risen and Yorkshire Housing has been well placed to meet demand. The </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">project </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">piloted a service </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ce</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ntre</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> telephone based Benefit and Money Advisor</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to run alongside the face to face service already in place</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">. The pilot gave Yorkshire Housing the opportunity to introduce a triage model to test the effectiveness of this way of working. The telephone based Be</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nefit and Money Advisor became a permanent position in August due to the success of the pilot.</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 19.67pt; padding-left:13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">“We have seen a considerable increase in the number of customers accessing the benefit and money advice service because they have no money available for food and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">/or utilities.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> The benefit and money advisors work with these customers to help them to access the growing network of food banks and other sources of emergency/charitable support to try to alleviate their crisis, e.g. arranging for some credit to be paid </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">onto their utility ‘keys’ for gas and electricity by a charitable </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">organisation or from Yorkshire Housing’s Tenant Support Fund.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">” Brian Davidson, Benefit and Money Advisor Team Leader.</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:5pt 0pt 5pt 22.33pt; padding-left:13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Welfare Reform Project Team is now working with the Benefit and </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Money Advisors review</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing their service</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, to shape </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">future delivery,</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> manage </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">demand and ensure </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> quality service is maintained</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> which needs to reach more customers</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> The Benefit and Money Advisors have so far identified </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">why and when </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">customers </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">present a need </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">for the service</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">so that a tailored approach to</span><span style="color:#111111; font-family:Arial; font-size:12