ures and cuts to services at a local level have increased the pressur</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e on Housing Providers to deliver social support services. The core business delivery could be affected and add pressure on staff at a local level reducing the amount of funds available for community engagement and enterprise activity.</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17pt; padding-left:13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Online access to ser</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">vices including training and support is a key concern and cannot be restricted to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> job centre plus access points.</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.33pt; padding-left:13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The local support frameworks could work but </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">need</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> extensive resource to become established</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17pt; padding-left:13pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">A </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">debt </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">protocol for Council Tax and Department </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of Work and Pensions benefit sanctions should be adopted</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">inline </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">with R</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">egistered </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">S</span><span